how to get simple count & group by in MongoDB?

assuming I have a data that has two categories, for example - football or basketball, where football value is 1 and basketball value is 2, and we have the following data:

_id    game
'1'      1
'2'      1
'3'      2
'4'      1
'5'      2

(the data contains football 3 times and basketball 2 times). I want to perform an aggregation that returns the following object:

{
   footballCount: 3,
   basketballCount: 2
}

I can't think of such an aggregation that results in such structure. How can I do that?
answer: `int i = doIt() / (j = 2);` , why the method execution comes before the grouping & accessing operators ?  they are in the top level of [Operator Precedence and Parentheses](http://stackoverflow.com/documentation/java/176/operators/9207/operator-precedence-and-parentheses#t=201701111907181800707) .thanks

answer: `filter-branch` only modifies (and copies) the branches (and tags) you specify. Once copied, you must force-push to any place you would normally push without force, because the copied commits are no longer historically-related to the original commits. So `git push -f <branch>`, or if you filtered all branches, `git push -f 'refs/heads/*:refs/heads/*'`. If you used a tag-name filter, you must force-push the tags as well, though this will be less successful if anyone else has an existing clone.
